text: The 2004 Australian federal election was held in Australia on 9 October 2004. All 150 seats in the House of Representatives and 40 seats in the 76-member Senate were up for election. The incumbent Liberal Party of Australia led by Prime Minister of Australia John Howard and coalition partner the National Party of Australia led by John Anderson beat the opposition Australian Labor Party led by Mark Latham. Until the 2025 federal election, this was the last time an Australian prime minister was re-elected. ==References== Category:2004 elections
title: 2004 Australian federal election
